"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-07-30-canada-appeal-cas-olympic-football-points-deduction\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - Canada appealed to the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) on Monday over the decision to dock them six points in the ongoing women's Paris Olympic football over a spying scandal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 157, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999942590421, \"rank\": 5.741039891447757e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Switzerland-based CAS said that Canada Soccer and the Canadian Olympic Committee had filed an appeal against the punishment handed down by football's world governing body FIFA at the weekend.\", \"from\": 204, \"to\": 399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 226, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.21168824392045e-28, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 240, \"end\": 253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CAS, sport's highest court, said a hearing was \\\"likely to take place\\\" on Tuesday with a verdict expected Wednesday.\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.21168824392045e-28, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reigning Olympic champions Canada were docked six points and fined 200,000 Swiss francs (over J$35 million) by FIFA after a staff member used a drone to spy on a rival team's training session last week.\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 545, \"end\": 551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999983176622, \"rank\": 1.4609168843592905e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.9999999990827746, \"rank\": 9.039235523414832e-10, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Analyst Joey Lombardi was given an eight-month suspended prison sentence and sent home by the team after being caught flying the drone over a New Zealand training session ahead of the game between the sides, which Canada won 2-1.\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 730, \"end\": 734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joey_Tribbiani\", \"score\": 0.9655073317700534, \"rank\": 0.02551307241419836, \"text\": \"Joey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joey_Tribbiani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joey_Tribbiani\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9830289838929789, \"rank\": 0.0097808241494473, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999983176622, \"rank\": 1.4609168843592905e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coach Bev Priestman and assistant coach Jasime Mander were banned by FIFA from all football-related activities for one year, along with Lombardi.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 959, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bev Priestman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\"}, {\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.9999999990827746, \"rank\": 9.039235523414832e-10, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The appeal to CAS does not relate to those bans, only to the points deduction.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.21168824392045e-28, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada's women have won both of their matches so far at the Paris Games, against New Zealand and France, but the penalty means they have zero points with only one Group A game remaining.\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999983176622, \"rank\": 1.4609168843592905e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9830289838929789, \"rank\": 0.0097808241494473, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9996310109332021, \"rank\": 0.00034325576854825075, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1343, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_AFF_Championship\", \"score\": 0.9999190122794508, \"rank\": 8.086079756541865e-05, \"text\": \"Group A\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_AFF_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_AFF_Championship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As it stands they must beat Colombia on Wednesday if they are to advance to the quarter-finals as they seek to repeat their gold medal triumph at the Tokyo Games three years ago.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998521494241984, \"rank\": 0.00014786994540924974, \"text\": \"Colombia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Priestman issued a letter of apology on Sunday and said she was \\\"absolutely heartbroken\\\" over the affair.\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Assistant coach Andy Spence, who like Priestman is from England, was put in interim charge of the team for Sunday's game against France, which Canada won 2-1 thanks to a Vanessa Gilles goal in the 12th minute of injury time.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Spence\", \"score\": 0.9999899697693844, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andy Spence\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Spence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Spence\"}, {\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9877716143010682, \"rank\": 0.00801743028408582, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9996310109332021, \"rank\": 0.00034325576854825075, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1798, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999983176622, \"rank\": 1.4609168843592905e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it is incredibly unfair to penalise the players in this way.\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The players had absolutely no control over the situation,\\\" captain Jessie Fleming said of the points deduction.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 2062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2018, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessie_Fleming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessie Fleming\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessie_Fleming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessie_Fleming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it has brought us closer [together].\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It feels like us against the world right now,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Golden Glory Paris Logo.\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2171, \"end\": 2183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_Glory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Golden Glory\", \"types\": [], \"wik